                "text": "Aeration is mixing of oxygen into the water. It increases the microbial growth in the water. The microbial growth acts on the organic matter and creates flocs which settle. The degradation of organic matter leads to the change in the pH of the water and production of gases like hydrogen sulfide which creates an odour.\nSo, the correct answer is option B."
