                "text": "One heartbeat in an average man lasts 0.8 second.\nHeart rate, also known as pulse, is the number of times a person's heart beats per minute. A normal heart rate depends on the individual, age, body size, heart conditions, whether the person is sitting or moving, medication use and even air temperature. Even emotions can have an impact on heart rate. For example, getting excited or scared can increase the heart rate. But, most importantly, getting fitter lowers the heart rate, by making heart muscles work more efficiently."
