        "answer": {
            "correctOptions": {
                "option": [
                    "3"
                ]
            },
            "solution": {
                "text": "The heart is the pumping organ of the body. It consists of four chambers i.e., the right auricle, left auricle, right ventricle and left ventricle. The right auricle receives the deoxygenated blood from the body and pumps it to right ventricle which in turn pumps it to the pulmonary artery. Whereas left auricle receives blood from lungs and pumps it to left ventricle from where it is pumped to the whole body through the aorta. Thus, the correct answer is option C."
            },
            "questionId": "5f13ec760cf25fd34822026d"
        }
