                "text": "In all vertebrates (animals having a backbone or spinal column) and a few invertebrates (animals lacking a backbone or spinal column), an iron-containing protein called haemoglobin is responsible for oxygen transport. Hemoglobin is a red pigment and gives the blood a red colour. The cockroach does not have haemoglobin. Rabbit and earthworms contain haemoglobin. Thus, option C is correct and other options are wrong."
