                "text": "A flower that lacks one or two of the four whorls is an incomplete flower.\nA complete flower has all four whorls calyx, corolla, stamens, and pistil are present.\nA unisexual flower has one of the reproductive organ either stamen or pistil is present.\nHomosexual flowers are not probable\nSo the correct option is \"Complete flowers\"."
